- N√∏rrebro

- 19:00‚Äì22:30 (just a few hours)

- Unpaid, but short, fun, and a chance to be part of a unique artistic project.

Falling Forward, Slightly is an experimental film about a swimmer, a fighter, and a dancer whose stories collide. It‚Äôs a passion project where we explore movement, sound, and atmosphere instead of dialogue.

We‚Äôve already been filming some beautiful scenes (see stills below), and now it‚Äôs time for the rave!

Skriptl√§nge pro Video: 40‚Äì60 Sekunden, ein Teleprompter ist vor Ort ‚Äì keine Auswendiglernerei notwendig.

Gesucht werden:
* 1 Schauspielerin & 1 Schauspieler
* Alter: 28‚Äì40 Jahre
* Look: authentisch, gepflegt, urban-professionell ‚Äì ein nat√ºrlicher ‚ÄûYoung Professional‚Äú-Vibe (Think: Start-up, Immobilienberater, Creator mit Vertrauensausstrahlung)
* Sprache: Hochdeutsch, sichere Sprechweise, gute Artikulation
* Erfahrung mit Kamera & Social Media Ads von Vorteil, aber keine Voraussetzung

√úber uns:

Wir sind die IMMO 4.0 GmbH, ein Performance-Marketing-Unternehmen aus Heidelberg.

Wir entwickeln Marketingkampagnen f√ºr Immobilienvertriebe, Bautr√§ger und Kapitalanlageprodukte im DACH-Raum ‚Äì und setzen dabei bewusst auf echtes, greifbares Storytelling mit professionellem UGC-Content.

Das bieten wir Dir:
* 500 ‚Ç¨ Pauschalgage
* Teleprompter + eingespielte Crew vor Ort
* Styling & Text-Input durch uns (kein Kost√ºm notwendig, clean/professionell reicht)
* Reelf√§hige Referenz f√ºr Deine Mappe
* Zusammenarbeit mit erfahrenem Videoteam in lockerer, produktiver Atmosph√§re

Bewerbung:

Bitte sende uns bis asap Deine Bewerbung mit:
* 2‚Äì3 aktuellen Bildern oder Showreel
* Kurzprofil (Name, Alter, Standort)
* Optional: Link zu Instagram / Agenturseite / Eigenen Reels
* Betreff: ‚ÄûUGC-Videodreh LEIPZIG ‚Äì Vorname Nachname‚Äú

Bewerbung bitte per WhatsApp an: +49 172 7042469

(Phillip Kirillov - IMMO4.0 GmbH)

Hinweis:

Die finalen Produktionen erscheinen im Rahmen einer Online-Marketingkampagne f√ºr den Bereich Kapitalanlage-Immobilien. Seri√∂s, hochwertig, glaubw√ºrdig.

Wir freuen uns auf Deine Bewerbung ‚Äì let‚Äôs create!

Dein Team von IMMO 4.0 GmbH

Hi @everyone 

Long shot but, thought I try. 

**LONDON - LEAD ROM-COM ACTRESS **

I want to try to make **10 episode vertical rom-com**, and looking for collaborative **actress 25-40** who would like to be a co-lead in the series. 

I have never made vertical drama project so this is just a fun, collaborative experience. 

The character is **typical rom-com lead, tall, attractive, native English-accent preferable but, not essential.  **

The episodes are about 1-2 mins long so, I believe we could film all 10 of them over one weekend, if not one whole day.

Mostly for **YouTube/TikTok and experience (unpaid). **

If you're interested, please DM me, and we can talk more. :)

how relevant are certificates gotten from Alison acting courses? and also how can I get an agent as a professional singer ?

topComments.text:
Not sure on Alison Acting courses‚Ä¶ ‚Äòprofessional‚Äô means you generally get paid for what you do, at which point the only reason to really get an agent is to fill up your work calendar a but more.

Should never pay an agent upfront, any reputable agent would take a cut per contract they get you.

Ever thought of doing weddings? Even though it might not be your thing, wedding singers can usually earn anywhere between ¬£200-¬£350 in a weekend. 
Same with tribute bands and/or cruises‚Ä¶cruises tend to pay a bit more.

Optagelserne foreg√•r p√• Thur√∏ i perioden 6.-9. november, og vil ligge idagstimerne i tidsrummet 9.00-16.00. Jobbet er ul√∏nnet, og man skal selv s√∏rge for transport til lokationen. Der vil v√¶re forplejning under optagelserne.  

Med i din ans√∏gning skal der v√¶re et selftape p√• max 2. min. med en impro-√∏velse som lyder som f√∏lger:

fort√¶l nu hovedpersonen, hvad den ting kan, og hvorfor lige pr√¶cis d√©n er s√• super fed at have som nybagt mor.

üé≠ **CASTING CALL ‚Äì New Australian Play in London** üé≠

We are casting **four roles** for an exciting new Australian play, *The Beat of the Bronzewing*, which will have a **showcase reading at the Hen & Chickens Theatre, Islington, on November 12th**.

üå™Ô∏è **About the Play:**
When Peggy shows up at Lorraine‚Äôs shack in dead-end tropical Australia, she brings an irresistible offer: a one-way ticket out of there. But with a cyclone looming and old wounds resurfacing, can Lorraine be convinced she has nothing to lose?

‚ú® Longlisted for the **Theatre 503 International Playwriting Award 2025**, *The Beat of the Bronzewing* explores the lives of three women in remote Australia, grappling with toxic femininity, domestic abuse, and rural isolation. Set against an evocative tropical landscape, the play is a gripping story of friendship, fear, and survival.

üë©‚Äçüé§ **The Team**
‚úçÔ∏è Writer & Producer: Charlotte Churcher
üé¨ Director: Chloe Cattin
ü§ù In partnership with the Australian Women‚Äôs Club London

üìÖ **Key Dates**
* **Auditions:** October 8th (12‚Äì5pm) at the Old Red Lion Theatre, Angel, Islington (alternative arrangements available if needed)
* **Rehearsals:** Sunday 9th November (10am‚Äì6pm) & Wednesday 12th November (from 2:30pm)
* **Showcase:** Tuesday 12th November at Hen & Chickens Theatre

üí∑ This is a **volunteer opportunity** with a ¬£50 contribution towards expenses.

items.text:
Hi everyone . I‚Äôve not posted in groups in a long time . I took a break from acting full time almost six years ago when I nearly lost my little girl nine times in one year  to an illness. 
I spent those six years, training , making connections and friends. Some directors, producers and writers from the likes of Netflix , Warner Bros, Lionsgate etc and some known actors . I wrote scripts that have now been sold to Lionsgate directors and being read by Pierce Brosnan, Samuel L Jackson and many more . 
I changed my whole outlook on acting and the industry and Instead for the last six years it‚Äôs been my only goal to help as many actors as I possibly can . I‚Äôve self funded features to help get as many actors and crew seen as I can , always circulating new actors and new crew every film. 
I spent the last six years building an acting curriculum and opened The Foundry Acting Studio after I not only exceeded spotlight approval by over three times but the studio is also SAG recognised too and soon to be other organisations. 
I‚Äôve had actors come to my class for three or four weeks and leave other major schools they were training at for three to four years. 

I offer in person. Online and one to ones. Which all information can be found on the page or by messaging The Foundry Page. 

I get it trust me . New acting classes , new showreel offers , new headshot specialists . There‚Äôs always doubt and to be honest what I‚Äôve noticed a lot recently in groups is a lot of hate , a lot of abuse and I‚Äôve seen people being attacked left , right and centre in this industry for posting a headshot or looking work. This industry is an absolutely amazing place , if we all pick each other up. So please keep your hate to yourself . All you‚Äôre doing is commenting and people are never going to work with you if you‚Äôre rude , foul mouthed or ignorant . 

So yes I understand people being weary of new things but I‚Äôm hoping we‚Äôve answered a lot below and again. Like the biggest schools out there.  I am spotlight approved , but I‚Äôm also the only independent studio in the U.K. to be SAG recognised and soon to be more . This proves legitimacy. 

So if you‚Äôre an actor or starting acting and you want real training , check out the post below. Also if you‚Äôre a good person , support other actors and pick people up rather than putting people down. Then you‚Äôll fit perfectly. 

Again . Help each other . Pick each other up. Support each other and be kind to each other . Show new actors that the industry can be a wonderful place . 

Also ‚Ä¶. We are the only acting studio making full industry professional feature films and we cast from our students. 

So message us now ‚Ä¶.. hope to meet a lot of you soon and keep being fantastic and pushing for that dream

sharedPost.text:
üé¨ The Foundry Acting Studio üé¨

Train. Work. Belong.

Where world-class coaching meets real screen credits.

At The Foundry, we don‚Äôt do hype, we do results. 

üìöOur coach is an internationally trained actor who paused his own career for five years to build a rigorous, modern curriculum from the ground up. (For the record: the world‚Äôs best acting coaches aren‚Äôt always front-of-camera stars, coaching and acting are different crafts. Ours happens to do both, and he‚Äôs now stepping back on set while leading this programme.)

‚úÖÔ∏èVerified. Recognised. Trusted.
 ‚Ä¢ Spotlight-approved training (and then some). When Spotlight reviewed our curriculum, it exceeded their requirements by roughly three times.
 ‚Ä¢ SAG-recognised. We‚Äôre one of very few independent UK studios to be both Spotlight-approved and SAG-recognised, with more professional bodies in progress.
 ‚Ä¢ Our curriculum has been reviewed by established actors, directors, producers and casting directors. Their feedback is consistent: ‚ÄúThis is the calibre you‚Äôd expect from a major, prestigious franchise school.‚Äù

‚úÖÔ∏èTraining that turns into work
 ‚Ä¢ We own our kit: RED cinema cameras, top-tier lenses, pro-grade sound, the works. No hired ‚Äúshowreel days.‚Äù
 ‚Ä¢ We produce our own professional features and shorts and cast from our students.
 ‚Ä¢ Speaking roles guaranteed in our in-house features/shorts for committed students who complete the pathway, because the goal isn‚Äôt just growth; it‚Äôs getting you working.

‚úÖÔ∏èAccessible. Supportive. Serious.
 ‚Ä¢ ¬£100 every four weeks for in-person classes or online classes.
 ‚Ä¢ We also offer one-to-one's intensives to go deeper, faster.
 ‚Ä¢ We welcome beginners, returners and working actors, and all different backgrounds. Whether you‚Äôre on a pension, benefits, full-time or part-time work, we‚Äôve designed this to be accessible and judgment-free. No nepotism. No gatekeeping. Just craft.

üé•Why actors choose The Foundry Acting Studio 
 ‚Ä¢ Curriculum: far beyond the minimum, Spotlight-approved √ó3.
 ‚Ä¢ Pathways: SAG-recognised, with additional organisations pending.
 ‚Ä¢ Industry connection: active relationships with professionals who‚Äôve worked across Netflix, Warner Bros., Lionsgate, FX, HBO, and more.

items.summary:
Hi everyone . I‚Äôve not posted in groups in a long time . I took a break from acting full time almost six years ago when I nearly lost my little girl nine times in one year  to an illness. 
I spent those six years, training , making connections and friends. Some directors, producers and writers from the likes of Netflix , Warner Bros, Lionsgate etc and some known actors . I wrote scripts that have now been sold to Lionsgate directors and being read by Pierce Brosnan, Samuel L Jackson and many more . 
I changed my whole outlook on acting and the industry and Instead for the last six years it‚Äôs been my only goal to help as many actors as I possibly can . I‚Äôve self funded features to help get as many actors and crew seen as I can , always circulating new actors and new crew every film. 
I spent the last six years building an acting curriculum and opened The Foundry Acting Studio after I not only exceeded spotlight approval by over three times but the studio is also SAG recognised too and soon to be other organisations. 
I‚Äôve had actors come to my class for three or four weeks and leave other major schools they were training at for three to four years. 

I offer in person. Online and one to ones. Which all information can be found on the page or by messaging The Foundry Page. 

I get it trust me . New acting classes , new showreel offers , new headshot specialists . There‚Äôs always doubt and to be honest what I‚Äôve noticed a lot recently in groups is a lot of hate , a lot of abuse and I‚Äôve seen people being attacked left , right and centre in this industry for posting a headshot or looking work. This industry is an absolutely amazing place , if we all pick each other up. So please keep your hate to yourself . All you‚Äôre doing is commenting and people are never going to work with you if you‚Äôre rude , foul mouthed or ignorant . 

So yes I understand people being weary of new things but I‚Äôm hoping we‚Äôve answered a lot below and again. Like the biggest schools out there.  I am spotlight approved , but I‚Äôm also the only independent studio in the U.K. to be SAG recognised and soon to be more . This proves legitimacy. 

So if you‚Äôre an actor or starting acting and you want real training , check out the post below. Also if you‚Äôre a good person , support other actors and pick people up rather than putting people down. Then you‚Äôll fit perfectly. 

Again . Help each other . Pick each other up. Support each other and be kind to each other . Show new actors that the industry can be a wonderful place . 

Also ‚Ä¶. We are the only acting studio making full industry professional feature films and we cast from our students. 

So message us now ‚Ä¶.. hope to meet a lot of you soon and keep being fantastic and pushing for that dream

Dancer & singers job advertisement and schedule

 Last Summer Jobs ‚Äì Dance & Sing Entertainer Under the Greek Sun! 

(EU citizens & non-EU residents with a valid EU residence permit welcome)

This is your last chance to land a paid summer job in paradise!

Palmera Entertainment is hiring for the final dancer and singer positions at 5‚òÖ resorts in the beautiful Greek Islands.

If you love the stage, sun, and sea ‚Äì this job is for you.

 Available Roles for male & female 

            ‚Ä¢     Entertainer ( kids, Sports )

 ‚Ä¢ Dancer / performer 

 ‚Ä¢ Singer / Performer

 Location: 5‚òÖ Hotels ‚Äì Greek Islands

 Contract Dates: August 1st ‚Äì October 31st, 2025

 Swiss employment contract

 Net Salary: from ‚Ç¨800/month + commissions ( depends on positions& experiences)

 We Offer:

 ‚Ä¢  Free accommodation

 ‚Ä¢  Full board (3 meals/day) + drinks included in the main restaurant 

 ‚Ä¢  Free transfer from airport to hotel

 ‚Ä¢  Free internet & laundry service 

 ‚Ä¢  Free uniforms

 ‚Ä¢  Free rehearsals and show training

 ‚Ä¢  ‚Ç¨200 travel bonus (paid at contract end)

 ‚Ä¢  Full insurance (accident, pension, social)

 ‚Ä¢  Extra bonuses for merchandising promo

 ‚Ä¢  An unforgettable summer experience

 Typical Workday (~8 hrs):

 ‚Ä¢ Morning: 09:45‚Äì12:30 ‚Äì Activities or kids club

 ‚Ä¢ Afternoon: 14:45‚Äì17:00 ‚Äì Sports, games, or creative sessions

 ‚Ä¢ Evening: 20:00‚Äì23:00 ‚Äì Mini disco, shows, social dancing

 ‚Ä¢  5-6 performances/week, 1 hour per show

 ‚Ä¢  Mini Disco: 2‚Äì3 times/week (20:15‚Äì21:00)

 ‚Ä¢  Main Break: 17:00‚Äì20:00

 ‚Ä¢  Rehearsals: As needed (usually midday)

Schedules can vary slightly by hotel and concept ‚Äì flexibility is key.

sharedPost.text:
Hi Everyone, 

We are currently looking for freelance dance and drama artists (aged 18-30) based in and around Derbyshire to take part in a well-known musical theatre show! - Reveal happening soon!
 
Auditions will be free to attend, and the chosen cast will be given fair compensation for all rehearsals and performances. This opportunity is aiming to provide valuable experiences to those of you who are struggling to find a way into the industry.
 
Rehearsals will commence in February 2026 on Tuesdays, Wednesdays and Thursdays from 10am-3pm in Chinley (High Peak); and shows are currently set to take place on the 19th, 20th and 21st March 2026 at New Mills Art Theatre.
 
If you are interested in taking part and want to find out more information, please sign up to our mailing list below: https://forms.gle/5FJyLNDdafigtWRn9 
 

 
I am also on the lookout for local people that have experience being a light and/or sound operator. These roles will be paid ¬£14.50 per hour and will be needed for 40 hours between the 9th and 21st March. 
Potential to work full-time at New Mills Art Theatre after successful show.
 
Please email me at molly.sodenfreeth@act2.org.uk if you have any further questions.

Come along and join us at Ilkley Playhouse for this amazing event starting on September 25th and until 27th‚Ä¶
PS I‚Äôm directing one of the EIGHT short plays but don‚Äôt let that put you off :-)

items.text:
# CASTING CALL: JOIN OUR ACTING PODCAST

When a group of actors sit around a table and use their spoken words to portray characters all going on an adventure together, that's called a tabletop roleplaying game (TTRPG). Our gaming group plays a variety of tabletop roleplaying games and publishes the audio as a podcast. Example famous ttrpg podcasts: Critical Role, The Adventure Zone, etc. We react as our character to the scenario presented by the game master. We respond to challenges, overcome obstacles, make jokes and laugh with our fellow acting friends. Would you enjoy acting in-character for a podcast audience? Join us.

# When we play:

Weekends. Both European and American time zones. Joining us doesn't commit you to every weekend. Instead, we pick games we want to try and sign up for those calendar spots.

# How long we play / what it‚Äôs like:

Our members sit at their microphones for four hours talking their way through an adventure using their words and laughter to entertain each other. We use theater of the mind, saying out loud how far away targets are instead of looking at combat maps on a screen. The recordings are high quality, and we air the audio as a podcast. Don‚Äôt worry, we don‚Äôt publish our names or faces.

# System played:

We get to learn and play a different tabletop roleplaying game (ttrpg) system each session. There‚Äôs no financial burden to you. The systems are either free to everyone or we were sent a free promotional copy from its creator.

# Oneshot or campaign:

Both. Like a traditional campaign, we repeatedly meet familiar non player characters (NPCs), facing challenges and experiencing long term character growth. We play our same character for a year. Our characters start at low power in January, grow to epic max fighting strength by December, then retire. Like a oneshot, each individual episode opens with a beginning to its plot, and the exploration of its story ends after four hours.

# Game Mastering (GMing):

We rotate so that everyone is invited to be a player and a game master if they want. The GM gets to pick which ttrpg we play that weekend. If you find a fun ttrpg you want to try, you can sign up as the GM and be confident that there will be players excited to play with you. If you prefer to be a player every time that‚Äôs cool, too. Our members don't have to GM ever if they want a break from it. Getting to pick how often you GM really helps relieve burnout. GM as often as makes you happy.

# You can vibe check past games:

We're on itunes, spotify, youtube, and all the podcast apps. Our cast rotates. Skip around and listen to snippets from a few episodes to see which of our members you want to play with first. The episodes aren't all great, but we have fun together. This isn't a job. It's a hobby, a way to relax and laugh meeting new people who slowly over time become lifelong friends. It's okay to miss games; you aren‚Äôt expected to be present for every session. The opt-in format naturally minimizes table trouble because you can see who‚Äôs signed up to GM and play in a game before you join it, and can pick dates that have people you‚Äôre looking forward to playing with.

# Joining:

To join, email us at FirebreathingKittensPodcast at gmail dot com and tell us about your equipment. Our minimum requirement is 24 bit audio (not 16 bit). If you don‚Äôt know what 24 bit audio means that‚Äôs not a problem, the new members tab of FirebreathingKittensPodcast dot com has an equipment section that explains what all the microphone words mean with pictures and videos. We welcome members of all experience levels and will train you. The new members tab also has info about our format and answers to frequently asked questions. Minimum age 21 years old. We reply to all emails from people who have 24 bit audio within three days with a support agreement for you to sign, and then will guide you through character creation and train you how to record great audio.

topComments.text: The opt in schedule is the best part. Play when you're available, don't worry about when you're not.

Production Type: Student / Non‚ÄëUnion

Safety: Child-actor compliant set: guardian required on set for minor.

Please submit resume, headshot, and demo reel (if applicable) to       Onlyforadaysf@gmail.com                  and indicate which role you‚Äôd like to be considered for. The selected actors will be sent sides with self-tape instructions.

Logline
A lonely Korean girl meets a magician hired to play her father for one day. A lie that becomes the most magical memory of her childhood.

Genre
Family Drama

Tone & Keywords
Warm, gently magical, grounded realism, themes of memory, identity, belonging, immigrant family, quiet humor.

ROLES
1) YUNSEUL / Ïú§Ïä¨ (Lead)
Female, 5-12, Korean. Sensitive, curious, and quietly lonely after moving to Canada. Hair‚Äëtwisting habit reveals anxiety. a believer who finds wonder in small things. The emotional heart of the film.
Language: English (primary), Korean (bonus).
Guardian: Parent/guardian required.

2) MAGICIAN (Lead)
Male, 25‚Äì35, Korean/Korean American. Witty on the surface, quietly lonely underneath. hides wounds behind jokes and tricks. A father‚Äëfor‚Äëa‚Äëday who is changed by Yunseul‚Äôs trust.
Language: English (primary), Korean (bonus).
Notes: Open to learning simple magic.

3) JUNGHEE / Ï†ïÌù¨ (Lead)
Female, 25‚Äì35, Korean/Korean‚Äëdescent. Protective, practical, and loving; carries guilt over the story she tells her daughter about the absent father. Hires the Magician out of fierce love and hope.
Language: English (primary), Korean (bonus).

4) CHUY (Supporting)
Male, 25‚Äì35, Korean/Korean‚Äëdescent. Playful ‚Äúuncle‚Äù energy, eases the mood with quick humor. Quietly honest protects the boundary of magic so it keeps its power.
Language: English (primary).

**Paid Studio Gig ‚Äì Surrey, BC (1‚Äì2 days, max 7 hrs/day)**

Hey Vancouver actors! We‚Äôre producing a batch of short videos for our brand (YouTube, Reels, TikTok, Facebook) and are looking for a confident on-camera presenter to record with us at our Surrey studio.

**What it is:**
* 1‚Äì2 studio days, max **7 hours per day**
* Scripted teleprompter reads + a few simple pickups/B-roll
* We provide the studio, teleprompter, and all gear
* **Contract provided** and **payment in full on wrap**

**You:** Comfortable on camera, friendly, clear delivery, can self-report to Surrey.

**Dates/Rate:** negotiable and flexable 

If you‚Äôre interested, please fill out this form, https://form.jotform.com/252610493666057 

with:
* Headshot + reel/links
* Your availability in **[date range]**
* A quick note confirming you can get to Surrey

Thanks! Excited to meet some local talent.

We are actively seeking talented BIPOC performers to bring beloved characters such as; Princess Tiana, Mulan, Mirabel, Jasmine, Moana, iconic Korean figures and more to life through engaging and authentic performances.

To our company representation matters! We are committed to celebrating the rich cultural heritage of these characters embodied by casting performers who reflect their backgrounds. Whether you're an experienced entertainer or a passionate newcomer, if you have a love for storytelling, performance, and creating magical moments for audiences of all ages, we invite you to join us in inspiring the next generation through inclusive and empowering portrayals.

Please PM Ever Enchanted Events or email everenchantedevent@gmail.com with a headshot, CV and a little about yourself and your backgroundü•∞‚≠êÔ∏è

üì¢Volunteers Wanted - Videographers! Liverpool Mystery Eventüì¢

CAJ Productions is looking for 2 more reliable volunteers to help with a one-off mystery stunt in Liverpool City Centre on Saturday 20th September 2025.

It's part of a brand-new UK theatre tour coming in 2026, and this will be one of our headline public marketing stunts. 

The role is simple, but really important:

. Filming the event (reactions) on a phone (2 people required)

What you'll get:

. Travel expenses covered

. Be part of an unusual, exciting event that's going to get a lot of attention

. Something different to talk about (and looks great on a CV for anyone in events, film, or theatre)

If you're free, reliable, and up for being part of something mysterious and fun, drop me a message here or comment below and I'll share the details.

Thanks! 

Charlie

Casting Call ‚Äì Voice Actors (Ul√∏nnet)

Hej alle,

Vi er et hold fra Masterclass p√• Potemkin ‚Äì Den Jyske Filmskole, som er i postproduktion p√• et sp√¶ndende projekt. Derfor s√∏ger vi nu stemmeskuespillere til to roller.

Logline:

En h√•befuld, men overset filminstrukt√∏r f√•r chancen i en branche styret af sequels og profit ‚Äì og m√• v√¶lge mellem at g√• p√• kompromis med sine v√¶rdier eller med sin karriere.

Vi s√∏ger:

 ‚Ä¢ Kvindestemme ‚Äì til at udlevere en Robertpris (kort ceremoniel replik - t√¶nk "And the Oscar goes to..."). Alder er underordnet.

 ‚Ä¢ Mandestemme ‚Äì til rollen som producer (kort telefondialogscene). Alder underordnet, da det er stemmen vi s√∏ger, men vi s√∏ger i omfanget af 25-39 √•r. 

Praktisk:

 ‚Ä¢ Projektet er ul√∏nnet, men alle medvirkende bliver krediteret i filmen.
        ‚Ä¢ Lydoptagelsen vil foreg√• i Potemkins lydstudie p√• Fredens Torv 3A, Aarhus C 8000.

Er du interesseret? Send mig en mail p√• simonthomaslange@gmail.com med en kort besked, eventuelt som lydoptaglese, s√• f√•r du flere detaljer :)

Vi gl√¶der os til at h√∏re fra dig!

**üîπ Bewerbung:**

Bitte sende uns so schnell wie m√∂glich Deine Bewerbung mit:

items.text:
CASTING CALL

We‚Äôre looking for a female actor to join us this December for our RAPUNZEL pantomime (school tour). 

We‚Äôre casting either of the following parts, with our existing performer playing the opposite role. 

- Rapunzel (lead)
- Gothel (villain)

Last year was our best selling tour - but we hope to beat that this year! Because it‚Äôs schools, the shows are weekday mornings and early afternoons, so you‚Äôll have your evenings and weekends free. The performances are in the Norfolk, Suffolk and Cambridge area. 

We‚Äôre currently offering a minimum of ¬£870 - which will go up as we get more bookings in + travel expenses. 
The tour spans from 1st - 19th December 2025. 
Aiming to start weekly rehearsals asap - in Hunstanton (PE36). These are unpaid but we keep them as flexible as possible.

This will be our thirteenth panto tour, and we‚Äôve built up a good name in the area, with schools booking us year after year (even before we announce the title!) We pride ourselves on being a warm, friendly, but professional company.

If interested, please get in touch for further details - either by a PM on here, or via email - purple-dreams@hotmail.co.uk - I‚Äôm looking forward to hearing from (some of) you üôÇ

Many thanks
Tobias Nicholls
Creative Director 
Purple Dreams Productions

items.text:
INTENSE CRIME DRAMA - SHORT (PAID)

1-day shoot in London (UK) for 2nd week in October 2025 (date tbc)

(For actors based in the London area).

 

Summary: A night of heavy drinking ends in a deadly contest between newfound besties - a fearless Nigerian gangland enforcer and a trigger-happy European gunman.

 

This project is Episode #0 of ‚ÄòBrave Hunter in Ghost City‚Äô  - introducing a new African story world and some of its main characters. ** **

 

MALE LEAD: to play fearless gangland enforcer.  Black African, 25-45, Lagos accent, 5‚Äô6‚Äù+, athletic physique with good fitness and conditioning. Stage combat training. Flat rate of ¬£300 for 15 hours.

 

MALE LEAD: to play trigger-happy gunman. White European,  35-45, 5‚Äô 6‚Äù+, 85kg-100kg,  powerful physique with good fitness and conditioning. Stage combat training. Flat rate of ¬£300 for 15 hours.

 

SUPPORTING MALE: to play dead gangster. White European, 35-45, 5‚Äô 6‚Äù+, 80kg-100kg. Half a day of shooting for ¬£150 for 7 hours.

 

You will need professional experience playing character roles on Stage, Film or TV. Please send in a cover letter, your CV with headshot and your showreel to Davina Brown at k2Filmworks@gmail.com

message.text: Manoj Kumar is celebrated as one of the most iconic and respected actors of Indian cinema. Known affectionately as ‚ÄúBharat Kumar‚Äù, he earned this title for his patriotic roles that inspired generations. With his dignified screen presence, soulful performances, and deep sense of social responsibility, he portrayed characters that upheld values of integrity, sacrifice, and love for the nation. Beyond his acting, he is admired for his direction and storytelling, which combined entertainment with strong messages of unity and moral courage. items.text:
Hello all, this is another post for a different student film happening on Auraria Campus. I am not involved in this one, I am posting to this group for the producer since he is not on Facebook. So if you are interested in this one please contact the producer. 

Producer- Brennan Jones bjones89@msudenver.edu 

Production Title- The Cost of Greed 

Production Dates- Exact dates are not set but filming will be in October 

Logline- Peter and Henry are sent on a treasure hunt to a house that is believed to be abandoned. Where they then discover it's not a treasure hunt after all and they must face their greed. Either take the treasure or leave empty handed. 

Peter (19-25) Male 

Peter has a moral compass that he deals with during this film. He wants to do the right thing and in the end that pays off for him. 

Henry (19-25) Male 

Henry is a billionaire with no need for more money, however that does not stop him from thinking he needs more. He is corrupt and in the end karma gets to him. 

Audition Dates- September 18th-September 29th

Audition Location- Email-Self Tape

This is a student film for a final project therefore this film is non paid and non union.

Contact Email- bjones89@msudenver.edu 

Must contact the producer to be consider for the role. Once you contact Brennan he will send you the audition material.

items.text:
Hello, we are currently casting for a student film on Auraria Campus! 

Producers- Isabella Coronado & Alanagh Finken 

Production Title- Normal Activity 

Production Dates- We don't have exact dates yet but we do know that we are filming in October. 

Logline- A mocumentary following a college's ghost hunting group as they prepare to explore a haunted local brewery's basement where a spirit has resided for the past thirty years. 

Alex (19-25) Male 

Alex is the leader of the ghost hunting group, he is very enthusiastic. He is clearly the one that is most devoted to this group. 

Chelsea (19-25) Female 

Chelsea is your typical girly girl likes being on camera but does not care about the club she is in. She is pretending to so that the club can get funding for the "haunted (not haunted) hot springs". 

Tommy (19-25) Male 

Tommy is very clearly apart of the club because he has eyes for Chelsea, he could not care less otherwise. 

Vera (19-25) Female 

Vera is Alex's sister and is only there because Alex believes they needed a fourth member and basically bribed Vera to join by saying she could borrow his car whenever she wants. 

Gary (45-55) Male 

Gary is the nightwatchmen for the brewery basement. He is very encouraging to Alex with his ghost hunting group. However that encouragement is not for reasons you think, Gary has a secret. 

Documentarian (20-30) Male, Female, Non Binary 

The documentarian is not really shown on camera, however they play a very important role. They are the voice we hear throughout the film asking questions to our characters, and making sarcastic and humorous remarks because they like everyone except Alex, thinks this club is utterly ridicules. 

Audition Dates- September 18th-September 29th 

Audition Location- Email-Self Tape 

This is a student film for a final project therefore this film is non paid and non union. 

**Contact Email- afinken1@msudenver.edu | icoronad@msudenver.edu **

**You must email both producers. Email the producers about your interest in the role and then we will send you the audition piece for your self tape. You must email to be considered, Facebook Messages does not count. **

items.text:
INTENSE CRIME DRAMA - SHORT (PAID)

1-day shoot in London (UK) for 2nd week in October 2025 (date tbc)

(For actors based in the London area).

 

Summary: A night of heavy drinking ends in a deadly contest between newfound besties - a fearless Nigerian gangland enforcer and a trigger-happy European gunman.

 

This project is Episode #0 of ‚ÄòBrave Hunter in Ghost City‚Äô  - introducing a new African story world and some of its main characters. ** **

 

MALE LEAD: to play fearless gangland enforcer.  Black African, 25-45, Lagos accent, 5‚Äô6‚Äù+, athletic physique with good fitness and conditioning. Stage combat training. Flat rate of ¬£300 for 15 hours.

 

MALE LEAD: to play trigger-happy gunman. White European,  35-45, 5‚Äô 6‚Äù+, 85kg-100kg,  powerful physique with good fitness and conditioning. Stage combat training. Flat rate of ¬£300 for 15 hours.

 

SUPPORTING MALE: to play dead gangster. White European, 35-45, 5‚Äô 6‚Äù+, 80kg-100kg. Half a day of shooting for ¬£150 for 7 hours.

 

You will need professional experience playing character roles on Stage, Film or TV. Please send in a cover letter, your CV with headshot and your showreel to Davina Brown at k2Filmworks@gmail.com

FEMALE PRESENTERS NEEDED IN CAPE TOWN

I need:

* White
* Coloured
* Indian
* Black
* Asian

Females to act as presenters for an amazing opportunity in Cape Town. This is a Permanent Position and we offer paid training if you pass Interviews.

After being trained you get R13 000 monthly for Presenter work.

If you in the ages 18years-35 years and from Cape Town, Can you Whatsapp me your full and half pictures and biography to:

068 644 2236
